  <!-- ═══ WHAT THE MODEL DOESN'T CAPTURE ═══ -->
  <h2>What This Model Doesn't Capture</h2>
  <p>No model is complete. Here's what a DCF inherently misses:</p>

  <h3>Upside risks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cycle breakout:</strong> If the memory and storage upcycle is more robust than expected, cash flows could exceed our 15% growth trajectory, pushing intrinsic value higher.</li>
    <li><strong>Structural margin improvements:</strong> Permanent cost optimizations executed during previous downturns could yield significantly better long-term profitability than historical norms.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Downside risks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cyclical severity:</strong> If memory demand unexpectedly crashes, FCF could easily fall back into deeply negative territory, rendering our base and growth rate assumptions invalid.</li>
    <li><strong>Market share loss:</strong> Increased competition in the global memory sector could lead to margin compression even in times of demand.</li>
  </ul>

